Find "Rockwell Software" on your computer. Click on "RSLogix 5000 Enterprise Series" to open a new controller file. Double-click on File to open a new file for the controller. The "File" button is located in the upper left-hand corner of the software. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/07\/Tenneng-1.png\/460px-Tenneng-1.png","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/0\/07\/Tenneng-1.png","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":134,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":221.56739811912226,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>\nLicense: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Click and select the CPU type "1756-L62 ControlLogix 5562" from the list. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/5\/52\/Tenneng-003.png\/460px-Tenneng-003.png","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/5\/52\/Tenneng-003.png","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":339,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":560.5,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>\nLicense: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Enter the project name "Industrial Garage Door Opener". Click and select the chassis type "1756-A7 7slot Controllogix 5562" from the list. Select the desired location for your file through Create In. Press OK to complete the project set-up.

Click on Data Types and then add a module to the "I/O configuration". Right click on "New Module" and then click on digital to highlights the modules. Add  the Input Module. Click and select "1756-IB16I" from the list. Click OK to open "Input Module Window". {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0b\/Tenneng-04.png\/460px-Tenneng-04.png","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/0\/0b\/Tenneng-04.png","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":283,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":467.6923076923077,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>\nLicense: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Enter the name "Input_DC". {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e3\/Tenneng-005.png\/460px-Tenneng-005.png","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/e\/e3\/Tenneng-005.png","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":505.27472527472526,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>\nLicense: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Click and select Slot "3" from the list. Click and select "Compatible Keying". Click OK to complete. Add the Output Module. Click and select "1756-OB16I" from the list. Click OK to open "Output Module Window". {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/75\/Tenneng-006.png\/460px-Tenneng-006.png","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/7\/75\/Tenneng-006.png","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":278,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":459.61367013372956,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>\nLicense: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Enter the name "Output_DC". {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/f3\/Tenneng-07.png\/460px-Tenneng-07.png","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/f\/f3\/Tenneng-07.png","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":266,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":439.3063583815029,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>\nLicense: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Click and select Slot "5" from the list. Click and select "Compatible Keying". Click OK to complete.
